  "text": "Interestingly, we observed that recombinant histone H3 citrullination was increased by both recombinant PAD2 and PAD4 at a mildly acidic pH of 6.4. This further confirmed the impact of bicarbonate was independent of pH since higher bicarbonate leads to more alkaline pH levels. Previous studies with a different substrate-Benzoyl l-arginine ethyl ester (BAEE) showed optimal pH of 7.6 for PAD4 [CITATION_1] . This difference is likely due to the different substrates used in experiments, as BAEE, unlike histone, is a small molecule substrate.",
